PART 1: WHAT IS SELENIUM (VIVA READY)
Selenium is a web automation tool
Used for testing web applications
Controls browser using WebDriver
Supports Chrome, Firefox, Edge
Works with Python, Java, etc.

👉 Keywords:

WebDriver = browser controller
Locator = find element
Action = interaction
Wait = handle delay
⚙️ PART 2: FULL SETUP (KALI LINUX)
✅ METHOD 1 (BEST – USE THIS)
Step 1:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3-venv -y
Step 2:
python3 -m venv selenium-env
Step 3:
source selenium-env/bin/activate
Step 4:
pip install selenium
Step 5:
sudo apt install chromium chromium-driver -y
⚠️ BACKUP METHOD (IF ERROR COMES)
pip3 install selenium --break-system-packages
🔁 Every time you open terminal:
source selenium-env/bin/activate
📂 HOW TO CREATE & RUN FILE
nano exp1.py

Paste code → Save (CTRL+O, ENTER, CTRL+X)

Run:

python exp1.py
